Aim: To demonstrate various list operations and related functions in Python.

Steps

Start the program.

Create a list list1 = [10, 20, "apple", "banana", 30, "grape"].

Display the original list.

Display the first element of the list using indexing [0].

Display the last element using negative indexing [-1].

Display elements from index 0 to 2 using slicing [0:3].

Display elements from index 2 to 4 using slicing [2:5].

Add a new element "Kiwi" to the list using append() and display the updated list.

Insert "orange" at position 4 using insert() and display the updated list.

Remove "banana" from the list using remove() and display the updated list.

Count the number of times "Kiwi" appears using count() and display it.

Remove the element at index 5 using pop() and display the updated list.

Reverse the list using reverse() and display the reversed list.

Find the index of "Kiwi" using index() and display it.

Clear all elements from the list using clear() and display the empty list.

Stop the program.



